<plot>This Pictorial short takes a look at the novel business of renting out male-escorts to lonely women in the New York City rent-a-guy establishment ran by Ted Peckham. The second subject treats Oriental art, in the making of cioisonne vases, prints and dolls, as practiced in 1939 by oriental craftsmen. The primary subject is a salute to the song "Thanks For the Memories" and it's composers, 'Leo Robin (I)' (qv) and 'Ralph Rainger' (qv).</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?423312</url></doc>
